{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Setting up an Xcode project that uses MapLibre Native for iOS."}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Getting Started","role":"article"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/AddMarkerSymbolExample"],"anchor":"Essentials","generated":true,"title":"Essentials"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Create a new iOS project","type":"heading","anchor":"Create-a-new-iOS-project","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a new (SwiftUI) iOS project with Xcode. Go to "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"File > New > Project…"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"text":"Add MapLibre Native as a dependency","type":"heading","anchor":"Add-MapLibre-Native-as-a-dependency","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"MapLibre Native for iOS is available on ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/cocoapods.org","type":"reference"},{"text":" and on the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/swiftpackageindex.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-gl-native-distribution","type":"reference"},{"text":" (for use with the Swift Package Manager). However, for this guide we will add the MapLibre Native as a package dependency directly.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Xcode, right click your project and select “Add Package Dependencies…”:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"AddPackageDependencies.png"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Paste the following URL and click Add Package:"}]},{"code":["https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-gl-native-distribution"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\